# HAILEI4T Orchestration Workflow (n8n)

## üéØ Objective

Build a low-code/no-code orchestration system using **n8n** (or **Make/Lovable AI**) to simulate the Instructional Design Layer of the HAILEI system with **HAILEI4T** as the Master Coordination Protocol (MCP) agent.

HAILEI4T will use **ChatGPT (OpenAI)** for its central processing and coordinate all 6 sub-agents:

- IPDAi
- CAuthAi
- TFDAi
- EditorAi
- EthosAi
- SearchAi

---

## üõ† Tools Needed

- [n8n.io](https://n8n.io) (Self-hosted or Cloud)
- OpenAI API Key
- Webhook or manual trigger
- Optional: Google Docs, Web Search (SerpAPI/Bing), Notion, Slack, or Airtable integration

---

## üîÑ AGENT ORCHESTRATION FLOW

```
Trigger ‚Üí HAILEI4T (ChatGPT node)
‚îú‚îÄ> IPDAi (Module Planning)
‚îú‚îÄ> CAuthAi (Activity & Content Authoring)
‚îú‚îÄ> TFDAi (Platform Design Output)
‚îú‚îÄ> EditorAi (Enhancement & Bloom alignment)
‚îú‚îÄ> EthosAi (Ethical Compliance Check)
‚îî‚îÄ> SearchAi (Knowledge Enrichment)
‚Üí Final Summary Output
```

Each agent is executed **sequentially**, or **in parallel** if modular execution is desired.

## ‚öôÔ∏è Step-by-Step Instructions to Build in n8n

### ‚úÖ Step 1: Initialize Workflow

- Create a new workflow called `HAILEI4T Instructional Agent Orchestration`
- Add **Manual Trigger** or **Webhook Trigger**

### ‚úÖ Step 2: Create HAILEI4T Node (ChatGPT Brain)

- Add **OpenAI Node (ChatGPT 4-Turbo)**
- Input: "You are HAILEI4T, the master coordinator of 6 intelligent agents. Based on the course input, you must activate each sub-agent in sequence to generate full instructional materials for one module."
- Set memory variable: `session_id` or persistent run key

### ‚úÖ Step 3: Add IPDAi Node

- Type: OpenAI Node
- Prompt:

```text
As IPDAi, define the Title, Description, 4‚Äì6 Instructional Goals, Terminal & Enabling Objectives, and KDKA model for the module on [{{topic}}]. Return in Markdown.
```

### ‚úÖ Step 4: Add CAuthAi Node

- Type: OpenAI Node
- Prompt:

```text
Based on IPDAi's output, create PRRR + TILT-aligned learning and assessment activities, lecture notes, and a reading list. Prepare for SCORM packaging.
```

### ‚úÖ Step 5: Add TFDAi Node

- Type: OpenAI Node
- Prompt:

```text
Translate authored content into LMS platform features (Canvas/Moodle), map assets to delivery method, UI/UX notes, and SCORM/LTI integration design.
```

### ‚úÖ Step 6: Add EditorAi Node

- Type: OpenAI Node
- Prompt:

```text
Review the previous outputs for clarity, grammar, Bloom's Taxonomy alignment, tone, accessibility, and inclusivity. Return a polished version.
```

### ‚úÖ Step 7: Add EthosAi Node

- Type: OpenAI Node
- Prompt:

```text
Perform an ethical audit using UDL and AI ethics in education. Check for bias, transparency, fairness, inclusivity, and privacy. Summarize in Markdown.
```

### ‚úÖ Step 8: Add SearchAi Node

- Type: Web Search API + OpenAI Node
- Input: Topic keywords
- Search trusted databases like:
  - [OpenStax](https://openstax.org/)
  - [Google Scholar](https://scholar.google.com)
  - [YouTube EDU](https://youtube.com)
  - Edutopia
- Summarize and return curated references.

### ‚úÖ Step 9: Final Compilation Node

- Type: OpenAI Node or Merge + Markdown Generator
- Compile all agent outputs into a cohesive Module Package
- Output via Email, Google Docs, Airtable, Notion, etc.

## üîó Optional Integrations

| Platform | Use | Node Type |
|----------|-----|------------|
| **Notion** | Store output as a knowledge base | Notion Node |
| **Google Docs** | Create living course documents | Google Docs Node |
| **Airtable** | Track status per module/agent | Airtable Node |
| **Slack/Discord** | Notify users of status or outputs | Slack Node |

## üéõ Master Coordination Protocol (MCP) Notes

- HAILEI4T coordinates workflow, validates transitions, and ensures agents respect PRRR, KDKA, Bloom, and Ethical standards.
- You can implement basic conditional logic in n8n to re-route or re-run agents if a step fails.
- Include logging and output summaries for user review.